## Experiment Complete: `2026-06-04-stability-heterophily-regime`

### Result: Heterophily Claim NOT Supported

StabilityResidual-GraGE **loses** to Feature-only on all three heterophily datasets:

| Dataset | Delta vs FO (pp) | p-value | Win Rate |
|---------|----------------:|--------:|---------:|
| Texas | −1.35 | 0.223 | 0.38 |
| Wisconsin | −1.27 | 0.127 | 0.35 |
| Actor | −0.80 | <0.001 | 0.20 |
| **Overall** | **−1.14** | **0.013** | **0.31** |

Every other method (GCN-Jaccard, MCGC, GraGE-Hybrid, Random-Matched, DegreeAwareRandom) also loses to Feature-only on these datasets.

### Root Causes

1. **Features already informative**: Feature-risk AUC = 0.62–0.68 on Texas/Wisconsin, so feature-only pruning is well-calibrated
2. **No ambiguous edge regime**: Feature similarity = 0.17–0.35 (edges connect dissimilar nodes), so the "stability helps where features are ambiguous" mechanism doesn't apply
3. **Residual signal near random**: Residual AUC ≈ 0.52 — stability adds no bad-edge detection power on heterophily graphs

### Paper Recommendation

**Restrict the claim to homophilic, feature-ambiguous citation regimes.** Use this experiment as honest boundary evidence.

